709409f-a.text:
804-808 (old Nos. 454-458) Sixth Ave., east side, between West 27th and 28th Streets. The centre portion of building (Moquins Restaurant) is a
4-story frame house.
About 1916.
Brown Brothers.

709406f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from W. 27th Street, showing the Sixth Avenue "El" demolition at that point. The 28th Street station appears preparatory to stripping. Across same appears an office building at the N.W. corner of this thoroughfare and W. 31st Street; the Hotel McAlpin and the Colonial Building. View No. 3 shows only the west side of this Avenue with
its various enterprises.
Jan. 20, 1939
Views: 1-2-3

P.L. Sperr

709407f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 27th Street, showing same before and after the demolition of the old "El" structure. The station seen is at 28th Sgreet. Note the streetcar under same. These were removed and transportation is now provided for by buses. The later view has the towering Empite State Building in its background.
January 29, 1928
March 29, 1939

P.L. Sperr

The same as above, from another angle.
P.L. Sperr  September 27, 1940
